# DISPARITY v33 playable demo followup batch.
# Format: point <key>|<domain>|<description>
point v33_point_01_collision_arena_bounds|CollisionTraversal|Arena collision solves are counted separately from visual bounds.
point v33_point_02_collision_blocker_volumes|CollisionTraversal|Blocker volumes stop the player instead of only clamping to the arena.
point v33_point_03_collision_sliding_resolution|CollisionTraversal|AABB collision resolution slides the player along the shallow axis.
point v33_point_04_traversal_vault_barriers|CollisionTraversal|Traversable low barriers can be vaulted or dashed through.
point v33_point_05_traversal_dash_cooldown|CollisionTraversal|Dash and vault traversal has cooldown telemetry.
point v33_point_06_traversal_visual_markers|CollisionTraversal|Traversal barriers render as readable public-demo markers.
point v33_point_07_traversal_verification_route|CollisionTraversal|Runtime verification exercises the collision/traversal route.
point v33_point_08_traversal_audio_feedback|CollisionTraversal|Traversal actions fire content-backed cue telemetry.
point v33_point_09_traversal_hud_telemetry|CollisionTraversal|HUD and director expose collision/traversal counts.
point v33_point_10_traversal_schema_baseline|CollisionTraversal|Schema and baselines require traversal coverage.
point v33_point_11_enemy_patrol_home|EnemyAI|Public-demo enemies patrol from authored home positions.
point v33_point_12_enemy_aggro_radius|EnemyAI|Enemies enter chase state inside an aggro radius.
point v33_point_13_enemy_chase_motion|EnemyAI|Enemies move toward the player while alerted.
point v33_point_14_enemy_contact_pressure|EnemyAI|Enemy contact drains stability and feeds pressure telemetry.
point v33_point_15_enemy_dash_evade|EnemyAI|Dash timing can evade or stun a chasing enemy.
point v33_point_16_enemy_failure_retry|EnemyAI|Enemy pressure can trigger the authored retry presentation.
point v33_point_17_enemy_visual_language|EnemyAI|Enemies draw vision rings and chase beams for public readability.
point v33_point_18_enemy_director_stats|EnemyAI|Demo Director exposes chase, evade, and contact counters.
point v33_point_19_enemy_verification_route|EnemyAI|Runtime verification deterministically exercises enemy behavior.
point v33_point_20_enemy_audio_cues|EnemyAI|Enemy contact and evade events use content-backed cue routing.
point v33_point_21_menu_pause_flow|GamepadMenu|A visible pause/menu flow can gate gameplay.
point v33_point_22_menu_completion_flow|GamepadMenu|Completion transitions the public demo into a completed menu state.
point v33_point_23_gamepad_xinput_loader|GamepadMenu|XInput is loaded dynamically without adding external dependencies.
point v33_point_24_gamepad_left_stick_move|GamepadMenu|Left stick contributes to player movement input.
point v33_point_25_gamepad_start_pause|GamepadMenu|Start button toggles pause/play menu state.
point v33_point_26_gamepad_a_traversal|GamepadMenu|A button maps to dash/vault traversal.
point v33_point_27_gamepad_runtime_simulation|GamepadMenu|Runtime verification simulates gamepad frames without hardware.
point v33_point_28_gamepad_hud_hint|GamepadMenu|HUD documents keyboard and controller play inputs.
point v33_point_29_gamepad_menu_metrics|GamepadMenu|Runtime report emits gamepad/menu counters.
point v33_point_30_gamepad_schema_baseline|GamepadMenu|Schema and baseline review require gamepad/menu coverage.
point v33_point_31_failure_overlay|FailurePresentation|Retry failure shows a dedicated overlay rather than only a status line.
point v33_point_32_failure_reason_text|FailurePresentation|Failure presentation stores and displays a reason string.
point v33_point_33_failure_checkpoint_return|FailurePresentation|Failure returns the player to the latest checkpoint.
point v33_point_34_failure_stability_recovery|FailurePresentation|Retry restores enough stability to continue play.
